---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Editorial Policy - ServerHi">
  <div class="container">
    <article class="legal-page">
      <header class="page-header fade-in-up">
        <h1 class="page-title">
          <span class="terminal-prompt"></span>
          Editorial Policy
        </h1>
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: June 18, 2026</p>
      </header>

      <div class="content-wrapper">
        <div class="legal-content fade-in-up">
          <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>Our Commitment to Quality</h2>
            <p>
              At ServerHi, we are committed to producing accurate, practical, and reliable tutorials
              for Linux server management, DevOps practices, and containerization. This editorial policy
              outlines the standards and processes that guide our content creation.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>Content Creation Standards</h2>
            <p>Every article published on ServerHi meets the following standards:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Tested Content:</strong> All commands, configurations, and code examples are tested in real environments before publication</li>
              <li><strong>Clear Instructions:</strong> Step-by-step tutorials with explanations of the "why" behind each step</li>
              <li><strong>Version Accuracy:</strong> Content specifies the software versions and OS distributions it applies to</li>
              <li><strong>Best Practices:</strong> We follow industry-standard approaches to security, performance, and maintainability</li>
              <li><strong>Regular Updates:</strong> Articles are reviewed and updated when software versions change or better methods emerge</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>Editorial Process</h2>
            <p>Our content follows a structured editorial workflow:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Topic Selection:</strong> Based on community requests, industry trends, and practical need</li>
              <li><strong>Research:</strong> Drawing from official documentation, real-world testing, and community knowledge</li>
              <li><strong>Drafting:</strong> Written by team members with direct experience in the topic area</li>
              <li><strong>Technical Review:</strong> Peer-reviewed by another team member who tests the instructions independently</li>
              <li><strong>Publication:</strong> Formatted, tagged, and published with appropriate metadata</li>
              <li><strong>Ongoing Maintenance:</strong> Monitored for accuracy and updated as needed</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>Independence & Transparency</h2>
            <p>
              ServerHi maintains editorial independence. Our tutorials and recommendations are based on
              technical merit, not commercial relationships. When we mention specific products, services,
              or tools, our assessment is based on our hands-on experience and objective evaluation.
            </p>
            <p>
              If we ever receive compensation, free services, or other benefits related to content
              creation, we will clearly disclose this in the relevant article.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>Corrections & Updates</h2>
            <p>
              We strive for accuracy, but technology evolves rapidly. If you find an error in our content:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Report it through our <a href="/contact">contact page</a></li>
              <li>We will investigate and correct confirmed errors promptly</li>
              <li>Significant corrections will be noted at the top of the article with the update date</li>
              <li>Articles display their original publication date and most recent update date</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>Authorship</h2>
            <p>
              Content on ServerHi is produced by our editorial team of Linux administrators, DevOps
              engineers, and technology educators. Individual articles may list a specific author,
              but all content is reviewed and approved by the editorial team before publication.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="legal-section">
            <h2>Contact the Editorial Team</h2>
            <p>For editorial inquiries, corrections, or content suggestions:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Email: <a href="mailto:editorial@serverhi.com">editorial@serverhi.com</a></li>
              <li>Contact Form: <a href="/contact">Contact Us</a></li>
            </ul>
          </section>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    padding: 2rem 0;
  }

  .page-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .page-title {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .last-updated {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-family: var(--font-code);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .legal-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .legal-section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .legal-section h2 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: var(--primary);
  }

  .legal-section h3 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .legal-section p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .legal-section ul {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-left: 2rem;
  }

  .legal-section li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .legal-section a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .legal-section a:hover {
    color: var(--primary);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  .legal-section strong {
    color: var(--text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .page-title {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .legal-section h2 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
